<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,720]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,624,648]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Externally this species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sawai Singh &amp; Gill)" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Sawai Singh &amp; Gill" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[722,1216,623,648]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ianagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis box="[722,952,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ianagallia bifurcata</emphasis>
(Sawai Singh &amp; Gill)
</taxonomicName>
in coloration. The asymmetrical subapical processes and structure of pygofer processes distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[1050,1165,660,684]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Austroagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distanti">
<emphasis box="[1050,1165,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. distanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from this and other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[232,385,696,720]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Austroagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,385,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Austroagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
